<l>iṭaiyoṟṟut toṭaru māytat toṭaru</l>
<l>naṭaiyā yiyala veṉmaṉār pulavar</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Scholars maintain that the ' semivowel-sequence words '</l>
<l>and the ' <foreign xml:lang="ta">āytam</foreign> sequence words ' follow the rule mentioned</l>
<l>above.<note
              place="foot">I.e., when iṭaiyorruttoṭar or āytattoṭar is the ' standing word ', the
          additional plosive does not appear, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">teḷku + kāl &gt; teḷkukāl
          ; eḵk + kaṭumai &gt; eḵkukaṭumai.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
